  "local_port": 53332,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on my Mac?",
  "response": "Completely removing Adobe CS6 from your Mac involves several steps to ensure all associated files are deleted. Here\u2019s a comprehensive guide:\n\n1. **Backup Your Data:**\n   - Before removing any files, ensure that any projects or important data are backed up.\n\n2. **Uninstall CS6 Applications:**\n   - Open the \u201cApplications\u201d folder on your Mac.\n   - Locate the Adobe CS6 application folder you want to uninstall (e.g., Photoshop CS6, Illustrator CS6, etc.).\n   - Open the application folder, and you should find an \u201cUninstall [Application Name]\u201d or an \u201cAdobe Uninstaller\u201d utility. \n   - Double-click the uninstaller and follow the on-screen instructions to remove the program.\n\n3. **Remove Adobe Common Files:**\n   - Open \u201cFinder\u201d and use the \u201cGo to Folder\u201d option in the \u201cGo\u201d menu (or press `Shift + Command + G`).\n   - Enter the following directories one by one and delete related Adobe files:\n     - `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/`\n     - `/Library/Application Support/Adobe/`\n     - `/Library/Preferences/`\n     - `~/Library/Preferences/`\n     - `~/Library/Caches/`\n     - `/Library/Application Support/`\n     - `~/Library/Application Support/`\n   - Look through these folders for any files or folders that have \u201cAdobe\u201d or the name of the CS6 applications and remove them.\n\n4. **Remove Adobe from Application Support:**\n   - Navigate to `~/Library/Application Support/Adobe/` and delete the files related to CS6.\n\n5. **Delete Preferences and Caches:**\n   - Navigate to `~/Library/Preferences/` and delete any Adobe preference files, often starting with \u201ccom.adobe.\u201d\n   - Navigate to `~/Library/Caches/` and remove any Adobe related cache files.\n\n6. **Remove Adobe Installers:**\n   - Check `/Applications/Utilities/Adobe Installers/` and remove any CS6 related installer files.\n\n7. **Remove Adobe Plugins:**\n   - Navigate to `~/Library/` and `/Library/` then look for any Adobe plugin files or folders that may still exist and remove them.\n\n8. **Check Startup Items:**\n   - Check `System Preferences > Users & Groups > Login Items` to ensure Adobe CS6 applications are not set to start automatically.\n\n9. **Clear Trash:**\n   - After removing all Adobe CS6 files, empty your Trash to permanently delete them from your system.\n\n10. **Reboot Your Mac:**\n    - Restart your Mac to ensure all the deletions are fully processed and that no Adobe processes are running in the background.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to remove Adobe CS6 completely from your Mac. If you encounter any issues, there may be third-party applications like AppCleaner that can help remove leftover files as well.",
